Label: MAP2K1
Comment: RANKL stimulation induces MEK1 phosphorylation in RAW264.7 cells

Label: SYK
Comment: RANKL stimulation induces SYK phosphorylation at Tyr-323 and Tyr-352 in mouse derived bone marrow cells and RAW264.7 cells

Label: TRAF6
Comment: TRAF6  undergoes polyubiquitination upon stimulation with RANKL which is further enhanced by IFN-gamma in mouse macrophage cell line RAW 264.7 and in mouse bone marrow derived macrophages.

Label: STAT1
Comment: RANKL stimulation induces STAT1 phosphorylation at Ser-727 in mouse pre-osteoclasts and bone marrow macrophages

Label: AKT1
Comment: AKT1 undergoes induced phosphorylation upon stimulation with RANKL at Thr-308 and Ser-473 in mouse bone marrow derived macrophages  and in maouse macrophage cell line, RAW264.7.

Label: NFKBIA
Comment: NFKBIA undergoes induced phosphorylation at Ser-32 in mouse bone marrow macrophages and in RAW264.7 cells.

Label: MAPK9
Comment: RANKL induces MAPK9 phosphorylation at Thr-183 and Tyr-185 in mouse bone marrow derived macrophages.

Label: PLCG1
Comment: RANKL stimulation induces PLCG1 phosphorylation in bone marrow derived macrophages and RAW264.7 cells.

Label: JUN
Comment: JUN undergoes induced phosphorylatin at Ser-63 and Ser-73 in mouse bone marrow derived macrophages, preosteoclasts and 293 cells. Amino acid residues 340-421 of TNFRSF11A are required for its activation

Label: PTK2
Comment: RANKL stimulation induces PTK2 phosphorylation in human umbilical vein endothelial (HUVEC) cells and RAW264.7 cells

Label: RELA
Comment: RELA undergoes induced phosphorylation at Ser-276 and Ser-536 upon stimulation with RANKL in mouse bone marrow macrophages.

Label: MAPK8
Comment: RANKL induces MAPK8 phosphorylation at Ser 183 and Tyr-185 in mouse bone marrow macrophages and preosteoclasts

Label: MAPK3
Comment: MAPK3 undergoes induced phosphorylation upon stimulation with RANKL at Thr-202 and Tyr-204 in mouse macrophage cell line, RAW264.7, mouse bone marrow derived macrophages, osteoclasts and dendritic cells.

Label: MAPK14
Comment: MAPK14  undergoes  phosphorylation at Thr-180 and Tyr-182 upon stimulation with RANKL in mouse bone marrow macrophages and pre osteoclasts.

Label: CHUK
Comment: CHUK undergoes induced phosphorylation upon stimulation with RANKL in human umbilical vein endothelial cells (HUVECs) and RAW264.7 cells

Label: MTOR
Comment: MTOR undergoes autophosphorylation upon stimulation with RANKL in osteoclasts and RAW264.7 murine macrophage cells.

Label: SRC
Comment: SRC undergoes induced phosphorylation at tyrosine residue upon stimulation with RANKL in murine bone marrow derived  macrophages, pre-osteoclasts and in RAW264.7 cells.

Label: TNFSF11
Comment: RANKL self associates to form a homotrimer.

Label: TNFRSF11A
Comment: TNFRSF11A self assembled through its cytoplasmic domain at position 534-539 and formed a trimer in HEK293 cells transfected with TANFRF11A

Label: CBL
Comment: RANKL stimulation induced the phosphorylation of CBL at Tyr-731 in mouse macrophage-like cell line, RAW264.7

Label: SQSTM1
Comment: TRAF6  undergoes polyubiquitination upon stimulation with RANKL which is further enhanced by IFN-gamma in mouse macrophage cell line RAW 264.7 and in mouse bone marrow derived macrophages.

Label: MAP3K14
Comment: RANKL stimulation leads to the activation of alternative NF-kappa B pathway which induced the formation of p52/RELB heterodimers through the activation of MAP3K14 (NIK). NIK deficient mice impairs RANKL mediated osteoclastogenesis.

Label: NFKB2
